<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM33150 - Shares to which
schemes can apply: Scheme shares</h1>
<br>
<p>An approved SAYE share option scheme must provide for directors
and employees to acquire shares ("scheme shares") which satisfy the
requirements of paragraphs 18-22 (paragraph 17(1)).
<br>
<br> Before a scheme is approved it is important to ensure that
tax relief will only be given for options granted and exercised in
respect of shares which satisfy the relevant requirements. Scheme
advisors should therefore:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">ensure that scheme rules define the scheme
shares precisely, such as "Ordinary &pound;1 shares in X Ltd which
satisfy paragraphs 18-22 Schedule 3". Where there is only one class
of share it would be acceptable to say "ordinary shares which
satisfy paragraphs 18-22 etc";</li>
<li class="filledcircle">ensure that in share option schemes the
options may only be exercised if the shares to be acquired satisfy
paragraphs 18-22;</li>
<li class="filledcircle">test that the shares intended to be

"scheme shares" do, in fact, satisfy the relevant requirements (see

below).</li>
</ul>
<p>Before a scheme is approved, to ensure that the intended "scheme

shares" do, in fact, satisfy the relevant requirements, scheme

advisors should:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">examine the Articles of Association of the

company whose shares are to be the "scheme shares" (to ensure that

the shares satisfy paragraphs 20 and 22)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">examine any shareholder agreements entered

into by employees or directors who may become participants in the

scheme, or to which they may be required to become party, which

would affect any "scheme shares" they might obtain (to ensure that

the shares satisfy paragraph 21)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">obtain a declaration from the company

establishing the scheme that, at the date of the application for

approval, the shares to be used in the scheme satisfy the

conditions in paragraphs 18-22 (see 

<a href="ESSUM33160.htm">ESSUM33160</a>).</li>
</ul>
